Revision history for Perl module Config::IniFile::Subst.

1.0.1 2026-06-24 Minor updates to build system; switched to
                 proper semantic versioning; removed deprecated signature.
1.0.0 2015-11-16 Removed minor bitrot, including references to $[
                   (causing possibly incompatibilty in programmes that
                   changed $[ globally; but nobody did that).
                 Implemented (finally) resolve_escapes pragma,
                   catching up once more with the C library.
                 Make code pass perlcritic --harsh (almost).
                 Expanded unit tests.
                 Switched to x.yyy versioning.
0.90  2011-03-02 Refactorisation from IniFile into Config::IniFile::Subst
                 Squashed bug not updating section names when
                   programmatically creating new sections.
                 Killed bug when explicitly addressing the unnamed section.
                 Unglitched non-standard-spelling section specifiers.
                 Comment lines read will be written to output file.
                 Added access to comment lines.
                 Removed load option nodeprecate (not a good idea).
                 Implemented (finally) include: and fallback: pragmata,
                   catching up with the C library.
0.12  2011-02-26 Removal of some bit rot.
                 Make code pass perlcritic --gentle.
                 Revamped test suite.
                 Deprecate fix_dir_delim and add_dir_delim.
                 Removed performance penalty on regexen
                   caused by use of $`, $& and $'.
                 As a consequence, now requires Perl 5.10.0.
                 Added load options nodeprecate, debug.
                 Removed bug that could cause LOGFILE/ERRFILE to
                   take their default values from some other file
                   than that containing the main programme.
                   ***INCOMPATIBLE CHANGE***
0.11  2003-10-01 Minor tweaks.
0.1   1999-09-04 Original version.
